{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/face-masks/penalties-not-wearing-face-masks","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"Penalties for not wearing a face masks","meta_description":"Penalties for breaching the general obligation to wear a face mask","content":{"processed":"<h2><strong>Regulations </strong></h2>\n<p>The Emergency Measures of the Ministry of Health states a general obligation to wear a face mask. This is monitored <strong>by municipal and also by state police forces</strong>. You can get a <strong>penalty up to 10,000 CZK</strong> if you fail to comply, however, the police can give you only a warning in case of a less major offence. The penalty is payable immediately, or later on during an administrative procedure.</p>\n<p>If you fail to comply with a quarantine or a self-isolation, it can be treated as <strong>a criminal offence</strong> of spreading a contagious illness.</p>\n<p><strong>Source </strong></p>\n<p>Police <strong>jurisdiction</strong> to monitor the public of wearing face masks is stated by a <a href=\"https://www.zakonyprolidi.cz/cs/2020-243\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external\">Special Law</a>. <strong>Penalties </strong>are stated by the Act No. 258/2000 Coll., <a href=\"https://www.zakonyprolidi.cz/cs/2000-258\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external\">on the protection of public health</a> (§ 92n, paragraph 1b of this Act), and by the Act No. 250/2016 Coll.,<a href=\"https://www.zakonyprolidi.cz/cs/2016-250\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external\">on the liability for offences and proceedings concerning them</a> (§ 91 of this Act).</p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/penalties-not-wearing-face-masks"},"changed":"2020-11-10T22:12:35+00:00","valid_from":"2020-02-25T00:00:00+01:00","langcode":"en","created":"2020-11-05T11:43:04+00:00","links":[],"relationships":{"region":[{"name":"All regions of Czechia"}],"icon":null,"situation_type":{"name":"Face masks","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"masks"}}},"measures":[],"related_situations":[{"title":"Outdoor","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/outdoor","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Indoor","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/indoor","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Types of protection","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/types-protection","langcode":"en"}}]},"questions_answers":[],"update":null,"valid_to":null,"last_updated":"2020-11-06T14:38:39+01:00"},"situationArea":{"name":"Face masks","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"masks"},"situation":[{"id":"6be143f8-c043-5b54-95e1-886da5127af0","title":"How to make a face mask","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/how-make-face-mask"}},{"id":"3243b8f0-b084-5582-ac1e-7d35b87dfcb2","title":"How to take care of the face mask","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/how-take-care-face-mask"}},{"id":"a381a51a-f9f2-576c-8f25-bbb26ccbe13b","title":"Types of protection","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/types-protection"}},{"id":"f5789357-2d5c-5761-8252-5d64918ad523","title":"What is the purpose of face masks?","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/what-purpose-face-masks"}},{"id":"e457350a-f7f6-52a8-a602-da6a8395f64e","title":"Outdoor","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/outdoor"}},{"id":"08a95b93-1efc-5883-84ec-4719394a3a18","title":"Indoor","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/indoor"}},{"id":"e4983126-2ff6-54b2-a538-5e2acb284360","title":"Penalties for not wearing a face masks","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/penalties-not-wearing-face-masks"}},{"id":"83b07e30-e658-5d3a-89fe-f47b1d0dc614","title":"Public transport, taxi","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/public-transport-taxi"}},{"id":"302631c6-2962-5f1a-8368-c9d5ebebd74b","title":"Traveling by car","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/traveling-car"}},{"id":"8fd695f8-ffa1-51e4-9469-a81d67e7b0f9","title":"Workplace","path":{"alias":"/situations/face-masks/workplace"}},{"id":"4f82b36e